<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8282324>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–3. Habitats (1–2) of Chalcovietnamicus lii (Lei & Peng, 2010) in Xishuangbanna (1) and C. weihangi sp. nov. in Guangxi (2); 3. C. weihangi sp. nov., female, prey on an ant (possibly Crematogaster sp.). Figures are copyright © Weihang Wang." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8282324/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8284243>
    dc:description "FIGURES 109–117. Chalcovietnamicus lii (Lei & Peng, 2010), male (112–113, 116–117) and female (109–111, 114–115) from Menglun, Xishuangbanna. 109–110. Habitus; 111. Posterior part of sternum, ventral view; 112–113. Palp, ventral (112) and retrolateral (113) view (modified from Wang & Li, 2022); 114. Epigynum, ventral view; 115. Vulva, dorsal view; 116–117. Embolus, in retrolateral (116) and ventral (117, slightly turning retrolaterally to show the EA) view. Abbreviations: aE = apical extension of embolus; EA = embolic apophysis; G = groove; SD = sperm duct." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8284243/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

